				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: New bard...  level 10<a name="69188"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 7 04 8:56 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hi there<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />   I am new also 
<br />

<br />
First things is how are your starting stats?  That could play a major dif on getting whacked.  Also what are you hunting?  Look also at your weapon dmg/dly.  The lower the delay the more chance you have to hit.  Not sure if you have a main or an alt that would help you to get a better weapon or no.  But check out the bazaar as well.  If you are short on money I see that people still do tailoring and silks are always needed and the hides.  Good place to go for that is in East Commonlands.  Set yourself as a trader and dont overprice and be patient is my opinion.  I keep an alt toon up in the bazaar that has foraged foods and stuff on it... people buy it.  That should help you to get at least some cash.  Simple suggestion for the forage goods is to change your macro for your forage so everytime you hit the up, down, side arrows (your pref) you forage... I took this a step further though and have a macro that does the ability and also puts it into my inventory.  look at your abilities and look at where it is... remember it goes from side to side 1,2 (top row), 3, 4 (middle), 5, 6 (bottom row)  simple macro is...
<br />

<br />
/autoinventory
<br />
/doability 2
<br />
/pause 5
<br />
/autoinventory
<br />

<br />
But point being is this is a great and versatile class as I am finding out. It can be frustrating starting out w/out a lil twinking I am sure (yeah, I was bad I started out with my lambent armor that my magi did for me) but the gear is not that expensive if you put a lil creative work into effect to make some plat <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />  
<br />

<br />
With a better weapon at least you will see yourself hitting the mobs a lot more:)  I cant give to much advise yet on playing because I have another thread going where I am asking a ton of questions on learning the toon.  Feel free to post there as well.  Maybe we can learn something new together.  Good Luck on your forays<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-11.gif" border="0" alt="Cool" hspace="2" />  </span></td>
