				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: New bard...  level 10<a name="71332"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 20 04 11:43 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Check you Intelligence and Dexterity, too.  Along with a low-low delay weapon, above-average stats here will improve your skills quickly.  Shop the Bazaar for a Sharpened Flotsam, which should be available for very cheap and is wicked fast and the Ratio is almost frightening - even if it Looks pretty sad.
<br />

<br />
And, more importantly, level 10 is about the last time that a Bard can pretend to be a Warrior.  After that, you have to be content with fighting like a Rogue, or a Ranger.  Let the 'real' tank take the hits, while you support the group with your songs, or debuff and damage the mob with your songs, or both.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
